General Install

Methods:

1) Debian Packages:
Install python-pip, python-virtualenv, and optional virtualenvwrapper

VirtualEnv Wrapper: Also could install with pip with optional install to .local
pip install virtualenvwrapper --install-option="--user"



2) Manual System Wide install
# Gets Distribute
 curl -O http://python-distribute.org/distribute_setup.py
$ python distribute_setup.py

# Gets Pip
$ curl -O https://github.com/pypa/pip/raw/master/contrib/get-pip.py
$ python get-pip.py

Still need Setup Tools and Pkg Resources 

3) Create single environment:
Untested, from http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/:
$ curl -O https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/raw/master/virtualenv.py
$ python virtualenv.py my_new_env
$ . my_new_env/bin/activate
(my_new_env)$ pip install ..

4) Pythonbrew
Install with pip from existing py install
Dependencies: 
libssl-dev
libreadline-dev
libsqlite3-dev - for ipython history
libbz2? 
libzlib1g-dev ?

If wrong source installed when switching between Py versions, delete pip cache in /tmp
